    "### Query 3. Every user name (first and last) in the music app history who listened to the song 'All Hands Against His Own'\n",
    "#### Comment:\n",
    "##### The CREATE TABLE query creates a table (users_by_song_played) which includes the following columns: song_title, user_id, first_name and last_name where song_title is the partition key and user_id is the clustering key (needed in order to retrieve all users)\n",
    "##### Then using INSERT INTO, data is added to the table\n",
    "##### The SELECT query is expected to retrieve every user for a given song_title value"
   ]
  },
